cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.CL, cs.GR 

This paper proposes a novel approach for text-to-image synthesis by inferring semantic layout. The approach involves generating object bounding boxes and refining each box by estimating object shapes inside the box. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper involves learning a direct mapping from text to image, which suggests that it may also belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) sub-category. The paper also involves natural language processing (cs.CL) as it deals with text-to-image synthesis. Finally, the paper involves graphics (cs.GR) as it generates images.
